{"title": "Cross-Cultural Handshake", "content": "If shaking hands isn't a culture-specific habit, it sure seems like it ought to be. So Science Fiction authors who are trying to be clever will come up with some other gesture for alien cultures to use for the same purpose.\n\nThe trouble is, shaking hands probably developed to its present form because it's a darned convenient thing for our human bodies to do. Obviously, other species have other ways of greeting each other, but the Media Watchdog would never let you show humanoids sniffing others genitalia. There are cultural differences in the way various groups go about the whole handshaking thing, but these are fairly subtle and the TV audience might not notice.\n\nAs a result, it seems like a lot of aliens shake hands by grasping each other's forearms, which is actually an old earth method of shaking hands, by showing that you have no weapons in your sleeves, as a display of trust.\n\nCompare Crazy Cultural Comparison. Misjudging this can lead to Greeting Gesture Confusion.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrossCulturalHandshake", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheBoxtrolls", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DemolitionMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ScaryMovie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Airplane", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MyEnemyMyAlly", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HumanxCommonwealth", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/AlanDeanFoster", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheConquerorsTrilogy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SnowCrash", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/XWingSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheLostFleet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarTrek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/LeonardNimoy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekEnterprise", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BabylonFive", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StargateSG1", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Andromeda", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/RedDwarf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MyHero", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MorkAndMi